				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What you can do is add the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PRG_RAM_circuit#Using_7420" class="postlink">same circuit that Family BASIC uses</a> to your NROM donor. Start by getting a 74HC20 and a 6264 or 62256 SRAM. I'd bet others can finish the explanation. If you can't do that, a mapper hack to SNROM is probably the best way to proceed, so long as you can find about 128 bytes of free space in $C000-$FFFF to insert code that sets up the MMC1 registers and copies 8K from ROM to RAM.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

