				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yogi, do you want to run this particular homebrew with SRAM support on hardware, or are you looking for an easy-to-use development platform for the NES?<br /><br />If the former, you can look into modifying the ROM to work with MMC1. In a nutshell, you would alter the reset routine to initialize the MMC1 and set up the expected banks, then jump to the original reset routine.<br /><br />If the latter, INL's boards and programmer are all you need. You can order them pre-populated with WRAM and pre-loaded with a mapper of your choice.</div>

